ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Looking
 at your reactions, you got 8 total — 5 likes and 3 "insightful" 
reactions. That's modest but not bad depending on your follower count.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">A few things worth noting from <strong>who</strong> reacted though — the quality looks solid:</p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Gabriel Masella</strong> – Football Data Scientist &amp; AI/ML Engineer</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Billy Mulley</strong> – Academy Scout at Tottenham Hotspur</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Luis Enrique</strong> – Scouting Director &amp; Sports Analyst</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Woody O'Brien</strong> – Aspiring Sports Data Scientist</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Your
 audience seems well-targeted (sports data/analytics niche). That's 
actually a good sign — the right people are seeing it, even if the 
volume is low.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">A few things that tend to boost engagement on LinkedIn:</p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Ask a question</strong> at the end of your post to prompt comments</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Post at peak times</strong> — Tuesday–Thursday, 8–10am or around lunch</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Tag relevant people or companies</strong> where appropriate</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Use a hook in the first line</strong> — LinkedIn cuts off text early, so the opener is everything</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Engage first</strong> — comment on others' posts before you post your own, so you're already visible</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">What was the post about? Happy to help you rework it or plan a better follow-up.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
