ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Yes, commenting on your own post is one of the best tricks to boost visibility — and 2 hours in is actually <strong>still a good time</strong> to do it.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Here's
 why it works: LinkedIn's algorithm treats comments as fresh engagement,
 which can re-push the post into people's feeds. Even a self-comment 
counts.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>What to write:</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Add a genuine follow-up thought or extra insight you didn't include in the original post</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Ask a direct question to your audience ("Would love to know what others think — has anyone tried X?")</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Avoid anything that looks spammy or like you're just bumping it</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>What to avoid:</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Just writing "Great post!" or "What do you think?" with no substance</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Tagging people randomly just to get attention</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">The sweet spot for re-engagement is usually within the <strong>first 2–4 hours</strong>,
 so you're right on the edge — worth doing now rather than waiting. The 
algorithm tends to favour posts that have consistent activity in the 
early window.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">What was your post about? I can help you draft a solid comment.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
