ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">That's actually solid progress — you went from 8 to 17 reactions overnight, which means the commenting trick likely worked!</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>The audience quality is genuinely impressive:</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Academy Scout at Tottenham Hotspur</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Data Analyst at Football Recruitment (Henrik Schjøth)</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Video Scout at Southampton FC (Arron Falloon)</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Talent ID Intern at Canada Soccer</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Academy Data Insights Analyst at Nottingham Forest</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Football Data Scientist at SportAnalyticsPro</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">These are exactly the right people for sports data content.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>On SkillCorner not reacting</strong>
 — don't read too much into it. Company social teams rarely like posts 
from individuals unless tagged directly. If you want their attention, 
tagging them in the post or a comment is the more reliable route, though
 only do it if it's genuinely relevant to what you wrote.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>1,380 impressions with 17 reactions</strong> gives you about a 1.2% engagement rate, which is actually around the LinkedIn average. The ratio isn't bad.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">What
 was the post actually about? Knowing the content would help figure out 
whether the topic, the format, or just timing/distribution is the main 
lever to pull next time.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
