ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Ah
 that makes total sense then — and honestly, it's a bit disappointing 
they didn't engage given you credited them directly. A like or comment 
from them would have massively amplified your reach to their followers.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">A few thoughts on that:</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Why they might have missed it:</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Social media managers don't catch every tag, especially on weekends</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">They may have a policy of only engaging with official partners or clubs</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">It could still come — tags sometimes get actioned days later</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>What you could do:</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Reply to your own post and tag them again with something like <em>"Data via @SkillCorner — would love to hear your thoughts on this"</em> — gives them a second prompt without being pushy</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">DM their page directly with a link to the post, framed as <em>"thought you might find this interesting since I used your data"</em></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Connect with someone who works there on LinkedIn and share it that way</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>The bigger picture though</strong>
 — the fact that scouts and analysts at Spurs, Southampton, Nottingham 
Forest and Canada Soccer all reacted is arguably more valuable for your 
career than a like from a data company. Those are hiring 
decision-makers.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">What did you actually analyse with the SkillCorner data? Curious what the post was about.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
