ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Great
 combo — off-ball runs and space creation is a relatively underexplored 
area compared to pressing metrics, so you're already differentiating 
yourself.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">For getting hired by a company <strong>like SkillCorner</strong>,
 they want to see that you can do what they do — turn raw tracking/event
 data into meaningful football intelligence. Your next project should 
signal that clearly.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Some directions that would resonate with a data company:</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>1. Extend your current work</strong>
Build on the off-ball runs project — add a model that ranks players by 
run quality, not just volume. Companies love seeing someone who can go 
deeper rather than just broader.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>2. Tracking data visualisation</strong>
SkillCorner's whole product is making tracking data interpretable. A 
project with really clean, professional visuals (pitch plots, 
animations, dashboards) shows you understand their output, not just 
their input.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>3. Build a metric from scratch</strong>
Define your own KPI — something like a "run threat index" — and validate
 it. This shows analytical thinking, not just technical execution.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>4. Combine event + tracking data</strong>
If you can merge StatsBomb open data with tracking data and produce 
something novel, that's very close to what these companies actually do 
day-to-day.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">What tools are you working with — Python, R, both? And do you have access to any data beyond SkillCorner?</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
