football analysis
data analytics
sports therapy / healthcare
You focus on understanding how players and teams create value, particularly through:
off-ball movement
transitions
spatial behaviour
Your work sits at the intersection of tactical insight and data-driven analysis, with a growing emphasis on tracking-derived data.
🎯 CORE STRENGTHS
Strong football understanding (tactical + positional)
Ability to translate data into actionable insights
Experience with both event and tracking-derived data
Clear and structured communication of findings
Analytical thinking developed through healthcare background
Understanding of physical performance and movement patterns
📊 PORTFOLIO PROJECTS
1️⃣ Off-Ball Movement &amp; Attacking Threat (Flagship)
👉 Focus: Understanding how off-ball runs contribute to attacking value
👉 Data: SkillCorner open data (A-League)
👉 Key elements:
classification of run types
xThreat attribution to off-ball movement
phase-of-play analysis (transitions vs settled play)
spatial analysis (start/end locations)
player profiling (per 90 metrics)
👉 Key insights:
cross-receiver runs generate the highest threat (~5x more than support runs)
transitions significantly increase run value
movement consistently progresses play into central high-value zones
👉 What it shows:
ability to work with tracking-derived data
strong storytelling and interpretation
understanding of off-ball dynamics
2️⃣ Regain → Progression Pipeline
👉 Focus: Linking defensive actions to attacking outcomes
👉 Key elements:
identification of regains
tracking progression after regains
analysing how teams convert defensive moments into attacks
👉 What it shows:
understanding of transitions
ability to build analytical pipelines
linking phases of play
3️⃣ Role Clustering Project
👉 Focus: Redefining player roles using data-driven methods
👉 Methods:
PCA
K-Means clustering
👉 Dataset: Top 5 European leagues (2023–24)
👉 Key elements:
feature engineering
dimensionality reduction
player role classification
👉 What it shows:
strong technical foundation
ability to apply machine learning methods
handling of larger datasets
⚽ PRACTICAL FOOTBALL EXPERIENCE
🟢 US Mondorf (Video Scout)
match analysis
player evaluation reports
tactical observation
real football environment exposure
👉 Demonstrates:
applied football understanding
ability to communicate insights in football language
🟢 Portland Thorns (Opposition Analysis Project – NWSL context)
structured opposition analysis
use of event data (IMPECT)
focus on key moments (regains, box entries, transitions)
presentation of findings to technical staff context
👉 Demonstrates:
ability to translate data into tactical insight
experience working within a professional analysis framework
🟢 Athenians FC (Player &amp; Board Involvement)
tactical awareness as a player
understanding of game structures
exposure to decision-making environment
🏥 ADDITIONAL BACKGROUND (UNIQUE EDGE)
Diabetes Specialist Nurse (NHS)
decision-making under pressure
pattern recognition from data
structured thinking and responsibility
communication with stakeholders
Sports Therapy Background
understanding of movement and biomechanics
insight into physical performance
awareness of load and fatigue
👉 This combination is highly relevant for:
tracking data analysis
physical-tactical integration
🧰 TECHNICAL SKILLS
Python (pandas, data analysis workflows)
Data visualisation (matplotlib, seaborn)
Machine learning basics (PCA, clustering)
Streamlit (interactive dashboards)
SQL (basic)
Tableau (basic)
🌐 PROJECT DELIVERY
GitHub portfolio with structured repositories
Streamlit application (interactive tool)
clear README documentation
ability to communicate insights in written form
🎯 CAREER GOAL
To work as a:
👉 Football Data Analyst / Research Analyst
Target environments:
data companies (priority)
SkillCorner
SciSports
Stats Perform
football clubs
hybrid analysis roles
Focus areas:
tracking data
off-ball movement
transitions
tactical behaviour
📈 CURRENT POSITION
Strong portfolio (above average for entry level)
Real football-related experience
Recently shortlisted for a role at SkillCorner
First LinkedIn project reached ~12,000 impressions
Actively building visibility and network
🧠 OVERALL POSITIONING
You are:
⭐ a data-driven football analyst with a clear niche in off-ball movement and transitions, combining analytical thinking, football understanding, and physical performance insight
💬 FINAL VERSION (SHORT PITCH)
If someone asks “what do you do?”:
👉 Use this:
I analyse how players and teams create attacking value using data, with a particular focus on off-ball movement and transitions, combining tracking and event data.</p><div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 right-0 h-12 bg-gradient-to-t from-bg-300 to-transparent pointer-events-none"></div></div><button class="pb-3 pt-1 text-xs text-text-500/80 hover:text-text-100 transition w-3/4 text-left rounded-lg">Show more</button></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><span class="text-text-500 text-xs flex items-center mr-2" data-state="closed">9 Apr</span><div class="flex items-center"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
