🎯 Why THIS is perfect for you
builds on your off-ball project
shows event + tactical understanding
connects to physical demands (SkillCorner language)
looks like real club work
differentiates you from most candidates
🧠 CORE IDEA (KEEP IT SIMPLE)
👉 Question:
❗ What happens immediately after a team loses the ball?
👉 Specifically:
how fast opponent progresses
how quickly pressure is applied
when the team is vulnerable
⚽ PROJECT GOAL
Identify whether a team is “structured” or “vulnerable” in the first 0–8 seconds after losing possession.
📊 YOUR METRIC (SIMPLE + STRONG)
👉 Recovery Demand Index (RDI)
Concept:
👉 Measures how difficult the defensive transition is
Formula (simple version):
👉 RDI = distance progressed × time until first pressure
Interpretation:
High RDI → dangerous transition (bad defending)
Low RDI → controlled transition (good defending)
🧠 WHAT MAKES THIS PROJECT STRONG
👉 You are:
not just describing data
not just plotting passes
👉 You are:
⭐ creating a football concept + metric
📊 KEY ANALYSIS BLOCKS
1️⃣ Transition Detection
find turnovers
define time window (0–8 sec)
2️⃣ Opponent Progression
distance gained
number of actions
speed of progression
3️⃣ Defensive Response
time to first pressure
defensive actions (tackle, duel, pressure)
4️⃣ RDI Calculation
compute for each transition
aggregate per match / phase
5️⃣ Tactical Insights
where transitions are dangerous
which players involved
how behaviour changes over time
📈 VISUALS (VERY IMPORTANT)
Keep it clean — max 3–4:
🔥 1. Scatter Plot
👉 X: time to pressure
👉 Y: distance progressed
→ shows vulnerability
🔥 2. Heatmap
👉 where dangerous transitions happen
🔥 3. Time Analysis
👉 early vs late game
🔥 4. Example Sequence (optional)
👉 1 real transition explained
🧠 YOUR UNIQUE EDGE (USE IT)
👉 This is where you win:
Add:
⭐ “Physical Load &amp; Tactical Decay”
Example insight:
Defensive response slows in final 15 minutes, increasing transition vulnerability.
👉 This links:
football
data
physiology
🧰 DATA SOURCE
✅ Use:
👉 StatsBomb open data (World Cup 2022)
Why:
high quality
relevant
recognizable
🧠 STRUCTURE (README)
You already know how to do this well.
Sections:
Project Summary
Problem
Approach
Metric (RDI explained clearly)
Key Insights
Visuals
Practical Application
Limitations
⚠️ IMPORTANT RULES
❌ DO NOT:
overcomplicate
add complex ML
build big system
✅ DO:
one strong idea
clear logic
clean visuals
football language
🏁 TIMELINE
Week 1:
👉 explore data + define logic
Week 2:
👉 analysis + visuals
Week 3:
👉 polish + README + publish
💬 FINAL TRUTH
👉 Project 1 = showed your level
👉 Project 2 = will show your thinking depth</p><div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 right-0 h-12 bg-gradient-to-t from-bg-300 to-transparent pointer-events-none"></div></div><button class="pb-3 pt-1 text-xs text-text-500/80 hover:text-text-100 transition w-3/4 text-left rounded-lg">Show more</button></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><span class="text-text-500 text-xs flex items-center mr-2" data-state="closed">9 Apr</span><div class="flex items-center"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
