ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">This
 is a really well thought out project concept. The RDI metric is the 
strongest part — you're not just describing what happened, you're 
creating a measurable concept with football logic behind it.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">A few honest thoughts:</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>What's genuinely strong:</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Creating your own metric immediately separates you from candidates who just plot passes</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">The Argentina 2022 World Cup dataset is recognisable and prestigious without being overused</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">The physiology angle 
(tactical decay in final 15 mins) is your unique edge — nobody else in 
the applicant pool has that background to draw on credibly</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">It naturally extends your transitions work from Project 2</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>One thing to tighten:</strong>
The RDI formula as written (distance × time to pressure) needs a bit 
more thought. Distance and time multiplied together gives you units that
 don't mean much intuitively. Consider whether it should be distance <strong>divided</strong>
 by time to pressure — so higher values mean more ground gained before 
pressure arrived. Cleaner logic, easier to explain to a recruiter.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>On Argentina specifically:</strong>
World Cup 2022 Argentina is a smart choice — they're champions, well 
studied, and Scaloni's transition structure was genuinely interesting 
tactically. Just make sure your insight goes beyond "they were good" — 
find something specific and slightly surprising.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Timing is perfect too</strong>
 — if the SkillCorner recruiter responds with feedback, you can 
incorporate it before publishing. That's a very smart sequencing.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">When are you planning to start?</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
