ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Honestly? <strong>Yours, and it's not close.</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">My suggestion (extending the A-League project into a run quality dashboard) was solid but essentially <em>more of the same</em>. It would deepen one project but not add a new dimension to your portfolio.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Your Transition Trigger idea is better because:</p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>It creates something new</strong> — the RDI is your concept, your logic, your name. That's memorable in an interview</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>It fills a gap</strong>
 — your portfolio has off-ball movement and role clustering, but a 
dedicated transition analysis with a custom metric adds a distinct third
 pillar</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>It speaks SkillCorner's language</strong> — their tracking data is heavily used for exactly this kind of physical-tactical integration</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>The physiology angle is yours alone</strong> — no other candidate at your level can write credibly about tactical decay and physical load from personal experience</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">The only thing I'd add to your plan is one sentence you can use when presenting it:</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><em>"I
 wanted to build a metric that a coach could act on immediately — not 
just describe what happened, but quantify how exposed a team was in the 
moments that matter most."</em></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">That framing — analyst thinking like a practitioner — is exactly what data companies want to hire.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Start with the data exploration this week while you wait for the recruiter's feedback. Good timing.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
