## 📌 Context
This project is part of a football data analysis portfolio and was developed within an academic/applied environment.
It should be interpreted as:
👉 an **applied opposition analysis project based on a professional scenario**, not official work with a club.
The goal is to replicate the type of analysis delivered in a real match preparation workflow.
---
## 🎯 Objective
To design a structured opposition analysis approach that:
- Identifies key opponent patterns  
- Analyses transition behaviours  
- Highlights tactical vulnerabilities  
- Translates data into **clear, actionable insights for coaches**
---
## ⚽ Scenario
- Playoff / knockout football context (high-stakes matches)  
- Focus on **moments that decide games**, rather than full-match general analysis  
---
## 📊 Data
- Event data (IMPECT-style dataset)
Main events used:
- Passes  
- Duels  
- Recoveries  
- Carries  
- Shots  
Derived focus on:
- Ball regains  
- Turnovers  
- Box entries (for and against)  
- Transition sequences  
---
## 🧠 Methodology
### 1. Key Game Moments
The analysis is built around four critical situations:
- Regains in opponent half  
- Turnovers in own half  
- Attacking box entries  
- Defensive box entries conceded  
---
### 2. Spatial Analysis
- Pitch divided into:
  - Corridors (left / central / right)  
  - Thirds (defensive / middle / attacking)  
Used to identify:
- Where actions occur  
- Directional tendencies  
---
### 3. Temporal Analysis
- Matches segmented into **15-minute intervals**
Used to detect:
- Changes in intensity  
- Late-game patterns or vulnerabilities  
---
### 4. Sequence Analysis
For each key moment:
- Events before and after were analysed  
Focus on:
- Build-up structure  
- Transition speed  
- Supporting actions  
---
## 🔍 Analytical Focus
The project prioritises answering:
- How does the opponent create danger?  
- When are they most vulnerable?  
- Where should they be targeted?  
---
## 📈 Output Style
The analysis is designed to be:
- Concise  
- Visual  
- Coach-friendly  
Focus on:
- Patterns  
- Tendencies  
- Vulnerabilities  
Not just raw metrics.
---
## 🎯 Expected Output
The final output should resemble a professional opposition report, including:
- Clear tactical insights  
- Simple visualisations  
- Direct recommendations for match preparation  
---
## ⚠️ Important Positioning
- This is **not official work with a football club**  
- No confidential or proprietary data is used  
- It is a **portfolio case study simulating real-world analysis**
---
## 🚀 Goal of This Case Study
To demonstrate the ability to:
- Think like a football analyst  
- Structure analysis around real match problems  
- Translate data into actionable insights  
This project is intended to be used for:
👉 GitHub portfolio  
👉 LinkedIn visibility  
👉 Applications to football data / analytics roles</p><div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 right-0 h-12 bg-gradient-to-t from-bg-300 to-transparent pointer-events-none"></div></div><button class="pb-3 pt-1 text-xs text-text-500/80 hover:text-text-100 transition w-3/4 text-left rounded-lg">Show more</button></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><span class="text-text-500 text-xs flex items-center mr-2" data-state="closed">9 Apr</span><div class="flex items-center"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
