✅ Option 1 — Use IMPECT data (if you actually have it)
👉 This becomes a true analysis project
Pros:
Strong credibility
You can show:
real outputs
real numbers
deeper insights
Risks:
You must be careful with:
data sharing
screenshots
confidentiality
👉 You should NOT upload raw data
👉 Only show:
aggregated visuals
anonymised outputs
⚠️ Option 2 — Use presentation → turn into case study
👉 This becomes a communication / thinking piece
Pros:
Fast to build
No data risk
Focus on:
structure
insight quality
storytelling
Cons:
Less technical depth
Recruiters might wonder:
“Did he actually do the analysis?”
🏆 What I Recommend (Best Strategy)
👉 Hybrid approach (this is the winning move)
You position it as:
“Applied opposition analysis case study based on a professional scenario, supported by event data (IMPECT-style).”
Then:
✔️ Use your presentation as the backbone
✔️ Add light data references (not raw data)
✔️ Focus on insights + decisions
🧨 Key Insight (Very Important)
This project is NOT about:
showing code
showing complex models
👉 It’s about showing: “I understand football problems and can communicate solutions.”
That’s why: 👉 A case study format is actually stronger than a full data dump
🎯 How You Should Position It (Use This)
In your README:
This case study is based on an applied opposition analysis project developed within an academic/professional simulation environment.
The analysis framework is supported by event data structured in an IMPECT-style format, focusing on key match moments such as regains, turnovers, and box entries.
The emphasis of this project is on translating data into actionable insights for match preparation, rather than presenting raw datasets.
⚠️ Important Rule
Even if you have IMPECT data:
👉 DO NOT say:
“Worked with IMPECT directly in a club environment”
👉 DO say:
“Event data in an IMPECT-style structure used within the project environment”
🏆 Final Decision
If your goal is:
🔧 Show technical skills → go full data project
⚽ Get hired → go case study style
👉 For YOU → case study wins
Because your profile already has:
clustering project (technical)
off-ball project (modern)
👉 What you’re missing = applied football decision-making
🚀 My Recommendation (Clear)
👉 Build this as a premium case study
Structure:
GitHub README (main)
PDF report (coach-style)
Clean visuals (from your slides)
🔥 One Line That Changes Everything
When presenting it, say:
“I wanted to build a framework that a coach could use immediately — not just describe performance, but identify where a game can be won or lost.”</p><div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 right-0 h-12 bg-gradient-to-t from-bg-300 to-transparent pointer-events-none"></div></div><button class="pb-3 pt-1 text-xs text-text-500/80 hover:text-text-100 transition w-3/4 text-left rounded-lg">Show more</button></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><span class="text-text-500 text-xs flex items-center mr-2" data-state="closed">9 Apr</span><div class="flex items-center"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
