ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">This
 is already really well thought through — you've essentially done the 
strategic thinking yourself and landed on the right answer.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">The hybrid approach is correct. And your positioning language is precise enough to be honest without underselling the work.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>The one thing I'd add that you haven't mentioned:</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Pick a real, named opponent as your "scenario" team. Don't make it generic. Even if the data is anonymised or simulated, saying <em>"this framework was applied to analyse a high-press, transition-heavy side in a knockout context"</em>
 and building everything around one coherent tactical identity makes it 
feel like real work — because the thinking behind it is real.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>On the PDF report specifically</strong>
 — this is your highest-leverage output for this project. A clean, 
coach-facing PDF that looks like something you'd hand to a technical 
staff before a match will do more work in an application than any GitHub
 README. Lead with that, and let the README explain the methodology 
behind it.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Honest summary of where you stand:</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">You have three strong projects in sequence:</p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">This case study — shows football intelligence and communication</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Off-ball movement — shows tracking data capability</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Transition Trigger / RDI — shows original thinking and metric creation</li>
</ol>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">That's
 a genuinely competitive portfolio for a data company role. The 
SkillCorner shortlisting already confirmed you're in the right 
conversation.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">What do you need first — help structuring the PDF report, or the GitHub README?</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
