ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">LinkedIn
 is fine as a hub but it has one big limitation — content gets buried 
quickly and recruiters can't get a clean overview of your work in one 
place.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">A
 personal website would take maybe a weekend to build and would give you
 something your competitors almost certainly don't have at early career 
level. A simple one-pager with:</p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Who you are (two sentences)</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Your niche (off-ball movement, transitions, tracking data)</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Three featured projects with visuals and links</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Contact / LinkedIn</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">That's it. Nothing fancy.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>The practical options:</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>GitHub Pages</strong> — free, you already have a GitHub, straightforward if you're comfortable with basic HTML or Markdown</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Notion</strong> — even simpler, looks clean, shareable link</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Wix/Squarespace</strong> — no coding, professional templates, small monthly cost</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Given your Python skills, GitHub Pages with a clean template would take a weekend and look more technical than a Wix site.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>The real argument for doing it now:</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">You're
 potentially going back and forth with a SkillCorner recruiter. If that 
conversation progresses, being able to send one link that shows 
everything — thesis, off-ball project, Streamlit app, opposition 
analysis, Portland Thorns context — is far more powerful than a LinkedIn
 profile where things are scattered across posts.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Want me to help you structure what the one-pager should look like?</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
  items-center
  justify-center
  relative
