ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Really glad you like it! Let me answer each thing directly.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>On the NHS — yes, keep it.</strong>
 It's your differentiator. Every other candidate applying to SkillCorner
 has a football background. Nobody else has pattern recognition and 
stakeholder communication trained in a high-stakes clinical environment.
 Frame it right and it's a strength, not a distraction.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>On Athenians — absolutely update it.</strong>
 Board member + tactical/video analyst is significantly more impressive 
than just "player." That shows you're trusted at decision-making level 
at a club, not just playing. Update it to reflect all three roles.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>What to do now, in order:</strong></p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Update two things on the site</strong>
 — your email and the Athenians description — then deploy it on GitHub 
Pages today. The sooner it's live the sooner you can share the link.</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Add the URL everywhere</strong> — LinkedIn headline, GitHub profile, every job application. One link that shows everything.</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Wait for the SkillCorner recruiter's feedback</strong> before starting the Portland Thorns case study. Whatever gap he identifies shapes what you build next.</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Post the clustering/MSc project on LinkedIn</strong>
 as a standalone post. You have a live Streamlit app — that's highly 
shareable content and most people in your network haven't seen it.</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Then build the Portland Thorns case study</strong>, followed by the Transition Trigger project.</li>
</ol>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>The honest big picture:</strong>
Your content is strong. The work is there. Right now the gap is 
packaging and visibility, and the website closes most of that gap 
immediately.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Shall I update the Athenians section now with the full role?</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
