ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Good catches on both. Let me address each:</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>On the LinkedIn URL:</strong>
The link I used was a guess. Go to your LinkedIn profile on desktop, copy the URL from the browser bar — it'll look like <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">linkedin.com/in/yourname</code> — and paste it here and I'll update it instantly.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>On the Portland Thorns project:</strong>
You're right to be cautious. Since you used IMPECT data, you should <strong>not</strong> upload the raw data or the actual analysis files. However you have two options:</p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>If you're building the case study version now</strong>
 — yes, this is exactly the project we planned. Once built with 
StatsBomb or public data framed in that style, that gets its own GitHub 
repo and links correctly from the site.</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>In the meantime</strong>
 — I'll remove the GitHub link from that project card and instead just 
present it as a portfolio case study with no repo link. It still shows 
on the site, just without a clickable link. That's honest and safe.</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>My recommendation right now:</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Remove the GitHub link from the Portland Thorns card temporarily</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Keep it visible on the site as a case study description</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Once you build the public version, add the repo link then</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Want me to make that change now alongside fixing the LinkedIn URL?</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
