ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Thank you! Yes, absolutely add it to LinkedIn — that's one of the best things you can do with it right now.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>How to add it to LinkedIn:</strong></p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Go to your LinkedIn profile</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>Edit profile</strong> (pencil icon)</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Scroll to the <strong>Contact info</strong> section → click the pencil</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Under <strong>Website</strong> → add your GitHub Pages URL</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Set the label to "Portfolio" rather than "Other"</li>
</ol>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">But first you need to <strong>deploy it so it has a live URL.</strong> Here's how to do that in about 5 minutes:</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Deploying on GitHub Pages:</strong></p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Go to github.com and create a <strong>new repository</strong> named exactly: <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">yiannis-kastritis.github.io</code></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Upload the <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">index.html</code> file I built you</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Go to <strong>Settings → Pages</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Under Source, select <strong>main branch</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Hit Save — your site will be live at <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">https://yiannis-kastritis.github.io</code> within a minute or two</li>
</ol>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Then use it everywhere:</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">LinkedIn contact info (as above)</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">LinkedIn headline — add "→ yiannis-kastritis.github.io"</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Every job application — paste the link alongside your CV</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">When you message the SkillCorner recruiter back — include it naturally</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Your GitHub profile bio</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">The URL <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">yiannis-kastritis.github.io</code> is clean, professional and free forever.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Do you want me to walk you through the GitHub upload steps in more detail?</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
