ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">No problem, it's simpler than it looks. Follow these steps:</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Step 1 — Create the repository</strong></p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Go to github.com and sign in</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click the <strong>+</strong> icon (top right) → <strong>New repository</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Name it exactly: <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">yiannis-kastritis.github.io</code></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Make sure it's set to <strong>Public</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Leave everything else as default</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>Create repository</strong></li>
</ol>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Step 2 — Upload the file</strong></p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Once inside the new repo, click <strong>Add file → Upload files</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Download the <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">index.html</code> file I built (from this chat)</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Drag it into the upload area on GitHub</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Scroll down and click <strong>Commit changes</strong></li>
</ol>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Step 3 — Enable GitHub Pages</strong></p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>Settings</strong> (top menu of the repo)</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Scroll down to <strong>Pages</strong> in the left sidebar</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Under <strong>Source</strong> → select <strong>Deploy from a branch</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Under <strong>Branch</strong> → select <strong>main</strong> → click <strong>Save</strong></li>
</ol>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Step 4 — Wait 2 minutes</strong>
GitHub will show you a green box saying:
<em>"Your site is live at <a class="underline underline underline-offset-2 decoration-1 decoration-current/40 hover:decoration-current focus:decoration-current" href="https://yiannis-kastritis.github.io/">https://yiannis-kastritis.github.io</a>"</em></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">That's it. Visit the URL and your portfolio is live.</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Let me know when you hit any step and I'll guide you through it. Which step are you on?</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
