## 1️⃣ HERO SECTION (Upgrade positioning)
### Replace current text:
"I analyse how players and teams create attacking value — with a particular focus on off-ball movement, transitions, and tracking-derived data."
### With:
"I analyse how teams create and concede value — with a focus on transitions, off-ball movement, and high-impact match moments."
---
## 2️⃣ OPPOSITION ANALYSIS PROJECT (CRITICAL UPGRADE)
### Replace current description with:
Applied opposition analysis project developed through Sports Data Campus, structured around a Portland Thorns (NWSL) scenario.
The analysis focused on high-impact match moments — regains, turnovers, and box entries — to identify how opponents create danger and where they are most vulnerable.
Key findings included:
- Rapid attacking sequences following high regains  
- Increased exposure after central turnovers in build-up phases  
- Clear attacking bias through specific pitch corridors  
- Late-game increase in defensive vulnerability  
The work was delivered as a coach-facing report, translating event data into clear tactical insights to support match preparation and decision-making.
---
## 3️⃣ ADD THIS FINAL LINE (VERY IMPORTANT)
Add at the end of the project description:
"Designed to replicate a coach-facing opposition report for match preparation."
---
## 4️⃣ OPTIONAL (STRONG UPGRADE — IF YOU WANT TO PUSH IT)
Add one short “impact-style” sentence:
"This project focuses on identifying where a game can be won or lost — not just describing performance."
---
# 🚀 RESULT
After these changes, your project will communicate:
- Football understanding ✅  
- Analytical structure ✅  
- Real-world application ✅  
