ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">These are good instincts overall. My honest assessment:</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Keep as-is:</strong>
The hero text change is actually a slight downgrade. "Create and concede
 value" is more generic than your current version. Your niche is 
off-ball movement and tracking data — that specificity is what makes you
 memorable. Keep the original.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Definitely do:</strong>
The opposition analysis description is much stronger with the bullet 
points — specific findings are always better than vague descriptions. 
This should go back on the site the moment you have the case study 
built, with that exact description.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>The two closing lines:</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><em>"Designed to replicate a coach-facing opposition report"</em> — yes, keep this, it handles the "but did you work directly with a club?" question before it's even asked</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><em>"This project focuses on identifying where a game can be won or lost"</em> — this is strong as a spoken line in an interview but slightly too salesy for a website. I'd leave it off.</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>The honest truth:</strong>
Most of these improvements are for the Portland Thorns project — which 
we've already removed from the site until it's built. So the smart move 
is:</p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Deploy the site as it is <strong>today</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Build the case study project properly</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Add it back with this improved description when it's ready</li>
</ol>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Don't delay going live waiting for perfect. The site is already strong.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Shall we get it deployed first?</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
