ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Yes — your Portland Thorns experience <strong>is</strong> still shown on the site, just in the right place. It appears in the <strong>Experience section</strong> (not Projects), described accurately as:</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><em>"Applied opposition analysis project developed through Sports Data Campus, structured around a Portland Thorns (NWSL) scenario."</em></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">So it's visible and credible — just not linked to a GitHub repo yet. Perfect positioning.</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Deployment steps — save these:</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Step 1 — Create the repo</strong></p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Go to github.com → sign in</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>+</strong> → <strong>New repository</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Name it exactly: <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">yiannis-kastritis.github.io</code></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Set to <strong>Public</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>Create repository</strong></li>
</ol>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Step 2 — Upload the file</strong></p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>Add file → Upload files</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Download the <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">index.html</code> from this chat</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Drag it into GitHub</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>Commit changes</strong></li>
</ol>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Step 3 — Enable Pages</strong></p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>Settings → Pages</strong> (left sidebar)</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Source → <strong>Deploy from a branch</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Branch → <strong>main</strong> → <strong>Save</strong></li>
</ol>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Step 4 — Wait 2 minutes</strong>
Your site is live at:
👉 <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">https://yiannis-kastritis.github.io</code></p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Then yes — use that URL everywhere:</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">LinkedIn contact info &amp; headline</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">CV header (next to email/phone)</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">GitHub profile bio</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Direct messages to recruiters like SkillCorner</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Go deploy it and come back when it's live. Then we start the Thorns project.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
