ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">That's
 a really positive response — and the fact he wrote in Greek is a great 
sign. He's engaging with you personally, not just professionally.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>What he's actually saying (translating the technical feedback):</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">He's impressed but pushing you to think deeper. Two specific challenges:</p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>xThreat 10-second horizon</strong>
 — xThreat models measure the probability of scoring within ~10 seconds 
of a possession event. His question is: if a run starts from a deep 
position, does it even reach the 10-second window to be captured? He's 
testing whether you understand the limitations of the metric you used.</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Context isolation</strong>
 — different runs happen in different game states. A support run in a 
finishing phase means something completely different to a support run in
 build-up. Can you isolate those contexts to give support runs fairer 
value? This is a genuinely sophisticated question.</li>
</ol>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>What "always ask one extra question" means:</strong>
He's coaching you. In your reply, don't just say thank you — ask him 
something back. That keeps the conversation alive and shows intellectual
 curiosity.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Your reply should:</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Thank him warmly (in Greek if you're comfortable)</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Acknowledge both limitations honestly — don't defend the project, show you understand the gaps</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Ask him one smart follow-up question</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Want me to draft that reply for you in both Greek and English?</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
