<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>It acknowledges both limitations honestly</strong> — you don't defend the project, you show you already thought about these gaps. That's exactly what he wants to see.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>The closing question</strong>
 asks how SkillCorner handles context in their own tracking models — 
which is smart because it shows genuine curiosity about their 
methodology, and it keeps the conversation going naturally.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>One tip before sending:</strong>
 if you want to make it feel even more personal, add his name at the 
start — "Geia sou [name]" — and feel free to adjust the Greek phrasing 
to match how you'd naturally write it. The most important thing is that 
it sounds like you, not a template.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
