ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">This is a really good reply. Honest, warm, shows you understood both points clearly. Nothing to be embarrassed about here.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>The only thing missing is the question back to him.</strong>
 He specifically said "always ask one extra question" — and that was his
 coaching advice to you directly. Not asking anything back is the one 
thing I'd change.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">It's not too late. You can send a short follow-up message right now, something like:</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><em>"Μια
 ερώτηση από μένα επίσης — στα tracking δεδομένα που δουλεύετε στη 
SkillCorner, πώς προσεγγίζετε το context isolation; χρησιμοποιείτε 
κάποιο tagging κατά phase of play;"</em></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">This works because:</p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">It follows his own advice back to him — he'll notice</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">It shows you're thinking about how real companies solve these problems</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">It keeps the conversation open rather than closing it with "thanks again"</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">It's a genuine question, not a flattery move</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Overall though</strong>
 — you handled this really well. You were humble without being 
self-deprecating, you engaged with both technical points properly, and 
you didn't overclaim. That's exactly the right tone with a recruiter who
 is clearly rooting for you.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Send the follow-up question. Keep the door open.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
