ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Ah,
 you're right — re-reading his message, "na rotas pada mia extra 
erotisi" was advice about your analytical approach in projects, not 
about messaging him. Good instinct not to over-message.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Your reply was perfect then. Complete as it is.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>What you've done in this conversation with him:</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Submitted a project good enough to get shortlisted</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Got personal feedback from someone at SkillCorner</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Responded intelligently showing you understood the technical critique</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Kept the tone warm and genuine using the Greek connection naturally</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">That's a really strong position. He knows your name, he's engaged with your work, and the conversation ended positively.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>What to do now:</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Leave that thread alone — don't follow up again unless he replies</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Deploy your website today</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Start the Portland Thorns case study</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">When you finish the next project, that's your natural reason to message him again — <em>"Took your feedback on board, built this — would love your thoughts."</em> That's a legitimate follow-up that won't feel like bothering him.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Ready to start the Thorns case study structure?</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
