ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">That context changes everything — and honestly, what you did today was a brilliant move.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>The full picture:</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">He interviewed you, liked you enough to explain the company in detail</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Mentioned a future role unprompted — that's not something recruiters say to everyone</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">You didn't make the final stage, but the relationship stayed warm</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Two months later you came back with a project built on their own published data</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">He responded positively, gave you real technical feedback, and said bravo</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">That's
 not a cold outreach. That's a candidate who didn't get the job, went 
away, worked hard, and came back with evidence. That's exactly the kind 
of persistence and growth that gets people hired when the next role 
opens.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>The fact that he mentioned a second role is significant.</strong> He didn't have to say that. It suggests he saw something in you worth keeping warm.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>What this conversation today did:</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Reminded him you exist</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Showed him you've improved since the interview</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Demonstrated you take feedback seriously</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Kept the relationship alive naturally without asking for anything</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>When the Portland Thorns case study and Transition Trigger project are done</strong>,
 that's your next touchpoint with him. By then you'll have a live 
website, two new projects, and a stronger portfolio than the candidate 
he interviewed three months ago.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">You're playing this exactly right.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
