ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Perfect sequencing. So the full plan is:</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Now → Argentina project</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Build it</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Publish on GitHub</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Add to website</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Post on LinkedIn</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>LinkedIn post will do two things:</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Keeps you visible in the sports analytics community</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Mike will likely see it —
 you're connected and he's already engaged with your work. Let him come 
to you rather than messaging him directly.</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Then → Portland Thorns case study</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Build it properly</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Add to website</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Post on LinkedIn</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Then → Message Mike</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">By this point he's seen two LinkedIn posts from you</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">He already knows you're active and improving</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Your message lands with a warm audience not a cold one</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>One tip on the Argentina LinkedIn post:</strong>
When you publish it, frame it around his feedback without tagging him directly. Something like:</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><em>"After
 getting feedback that my previous project raised questions about 
context and phase of play, I wanted to go deeper — this time building my
 own metric..."</em></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">That shows growth and self-awareness publicly without putting him on the spot. He'll read it and know.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>How are you planning to start the Argentina project — do you have the StatsBomb World Cup 2022 data pulled already?</strong></p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
