ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Haha
 fair point! That's just because your browser saved multiple versions — 
index.html, index(1).html, index(2).html, index(3).html.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Easy fix — two options:</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Option 1 — Rename before uploading (simplest)</strong></p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Find the file on your phone/computer</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Long press or right click → <strong>Rename</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Name it exactly: <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">index.html</code></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Upload that to GitHub</li>
</ol>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Option 2 — If already uploaded to GitHub</strong></p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Go to your repo on GitHub</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click the file → click the <strong>pencil icon</strong> (edit)</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">At the top where the filename shows, clear it and type <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">index.html</code></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Commit changes</li>
</ol>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>The file must be named exactly <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">index.html</code></strong> for GitHub Pages to recognise it as your homepage. Any other name and the site won't load correctly.</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Also — once it's live at <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">https://yiannis-kastritis.github.io</code>
 the URL itself looks completely professional. Nobody will ever see the 
filename. That's only visible when downloading from this chat.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Have you created the GitHub repo yet?</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
