ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Exactly right. Here's the full picture:</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Project 3 — Argentina 2022 (Public)</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Regain → Progression metric applied to Argentina AND their opponents</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">For and against comparison per match</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Shows the metric working on a prestigious public dataset</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Answers Mike's feedback directly</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Published on GitHub + LinkedIn</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Project 4 — Portland Thorns Case Study (Public)</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Same metric, same framework</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Applied in an opposition analysis context</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Coach-facing output — PDF report style</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Shows the metric used for real analytical decision-making</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Published on GitHub + LinkedIn</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>The story this tells:</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><em>"I
 built a metric for real opposition analysis work, validated it publicly
 on World Cup data, then showed how it functions inside a professional 
match preparation workflow."</em></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">That's three connected things:</p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Tool creation (metric built for Thorns)</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Academic validation (Argentina/StatsBomb)</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Professional application (Thorns case study)</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Practical sequencing:</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Do Argentina first because:</p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">StatsBomb data is free and clean</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">No confidentiality concerns</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Builds your confidence with the metric publicly</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Then Thorns case study becomes the natural "applied" follow-up</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Right now the immediate next step is simple:</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Get back to Colab, run the StatsBomb setup we started, and find the World Cup 2022 competition ID.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Shall we continue from where we left off?</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
