          ease-[cubic-bezier(0.165,0.85,0.45,1)] h-8 w-8 rounded-md backdrop-blur-md _fill_10ocf_9 _ghost_10ocf_96" type="button" aria-label="Copy to clipboard" data-state="closed"><div class="relative"><div class="transition-all opacity-100 scale-100" style="width: 20px; height: 20px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" style="flex-shrink: 0;" class="transition-all opacity-100 scale-100" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M12.5 3A1.5 1.5 0 0 1 14 4.5V6h1.5A1.5 1.5 0 0 1 17 7.5v8a1.5 1.5 0 0 1-1.5 1.5h-8A1.5 1.5 0 0 1 6 15.5V14H4.5A1.5 1.5 0 0 1 3 12.5v-8A1.5 1.5 0 0 1 4.5 3zm1.5 9.5a1.5 1.5 0 0 1-1.5 1.5H7v1.5a.5.5 0 0 0 .5.5h8a.5.5 0 0 0 .5-.5v-8a.5.5 0 0 0-.5-.5H14zM4.5 4a.5.5 0 0 0-.5.5v8a.5.5 0 0 0 .5.5h8a.5.5 0 0 0 .5-.5v-8a.5.5 0 0 0-.5-.5z"></path></svg></div><div class="absolute inset-0 flex items-center justify-center"><div class="transition-all opacity-0 scale-50" style="width: 20px; height: 20px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" style="flex-shrink: 0;" class="transition-all opacity-0 scale-50" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M15.188 5.11a.5.5 0 0 1 .752.626l-.056.084-7.5 9a.5.5 0 0 1-.738.033l-3.5-3.5-.064-.078a.501.501 0 0 1 .693-.693l.078.064 3.113 3.113 7.15-8.58z"></path></svg></div></div></div></button></div></div><div class="text-text-500 font-small p-3.5 pb-0">markdown</div><div class="overflow-x-auto"><pre class="code-block__code !my-0 !rounded-lg !text-sm !leading-relaxed p-3.5" style="color: rgb(20, 24, 31); background: transparent; font-family: var(--font-mono);"><code class="language-markdown" style="color: rgb(20, 24, 31); background: transparent; font-family: var(--font-mono); white-space: pre;"><span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59); font-weight: bold;">#</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(184, 10, 24); font-weight: bold;"> Defensive Transitions &amp; Progression Analysis — Argentina 2022 World Cup</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59); font-weight: bold;">##</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(184, 10, 24); font-weight: bold;"> Project Overview</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span>This project applies a custom-built Regain → Progression metric to Argentina's 
</span><span>2022 FIFA World Cup campaign using StatsBomb open event data.
</span><span>
</span><span>The central question is simple:
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">What happens in the first 5 seconds after a team wins the ball back?</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span>The metric was originally developed as part of an applied opposition analysis 
</span><span>workflow. This project validates it publicly on a high-profile dataset, while 
</span><span>directly addressing a core analytical challenge: how do we measure the quality 
</span><span>of defensive transitions, not just their frequency?
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token hr" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">---</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59); font-weight: bold;">##</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(184, 10, 24); font-weight: bold;"> Research Question</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token blockquote" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">&gt;</span><span> How efficiently do teams convert defensive actions into forward progression 
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token blockquote" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">&gt;</span><span> in the immediate transition window — and how does this vary by match, 
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token blockquote" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">&gt;</span><span> phase of play, and opponent?
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token hr" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">---</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59); font-weight: bold;">##</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(184, 10, 24); font-weight: bold;"> Metric — Regain Progression Index (RPI)</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59); font-weight: bold;">###</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(184, 10, 24); font-weight: bold;"> Definition</span><span>
</span></span><span><span>The </span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Regain Progression Index (RPI)</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span> measures how effectively a team 
</span></span><span>advances the ball in the 5 seconds immediately following a regain of possession.
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59); font-weight: bold;">###</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(184, 10, 24); font-weight: bold;"> What counts as a regain?</span><span>
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> Interceptions
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> Tackles won
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> Ball recoveries
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> Goalkeeper claims
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59); font-weight: bold;">###</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(184, 10, 24); font-weight: bold;"> What counts as progression?</span><span>
</span></span><span>Any subsequent event within 5 seconds of the regain that moves the ball:
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> </span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Forward</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span> — toward the opponent's goal
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> </span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Lateral</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span> — sideways across the pitch (maintaining threat)
</span></span><span>
</span><span>Backward passes and clearances are excluded — they represent defensive 
</span><span>consolidation, not transition threat.
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59); font-weight: bold;">###</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(184, 10, 24); font-weight: bold;"> RPI Formula</span></span></code></pre></div></div>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">RPI = (Progressive actions within 5s) / (Total regains)</p>
<div role="group" aria-label="Code" tabindex="0" class="relative group/copy bg-bg-000/50 border-0.5 border-border-400 rounded-lg focus:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-accent-100"><div class="sticky opacity-0 group-hover/copy:opacity-100 group-focus-within/copy:opacity-100 top-2 py-2 h-12 w-0 float-right"><div class="absolute right-0 h-8 px-2 items-center inline-flex z-10"><button class="inline-flex
  items-center
  justify-center
  relative
  isolate
  shrink-0
  can-focus
  select-none
  disabled:pointer-events-none
  disabled:opacity-50
  disabled:shadow-none
  disabled:drop-shadow-none border-transparent
          transition
          font-base
          duration-300
          ease-[cubic-bezier(0.165,0.85,0.45,1)] h-8 w-8 rounded-md backdrop-blur-md _fill_10ocf_9 _ghost_10ocf_96" type="button" aria-label="Copy to clipboard" data-state="closed"><div class="relative"><div class="transition-all opacity-100 scale-100" style="width: 20px; height: 20px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" style="flex-shrink: 0;" class="transition-all opacity-100 scale-100" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M12.5 3A1.5 1.5 0 0 1 14 4.5V6h1.5A1.5 1.5 0 0 1 17 7.5v8a1.5 1.5 0 0 1-1.5 1.5h-8A1.5 1.5 0 0 1 6 15.5V14H4.5A1.5 1.5 0 0 1 3 12.5v-8A1.5 1.5 0 0 1 4.5 3zm1.5 9.5a1.5 1.5 0 0 1-1.5 1.5H7v1.5a.5.5 0 0 0 .5.5h8a.5.5 0 0 0 .5-.5v-8a.5.5 0 0 0-.5-.5H14zM4.5 4a.5.5 0 0 0-.5.5v8a.5.5 0 0 0 .5.5h8a.5.5 0 0 0 .5-.5v-8a.5.5 0 0 0-.5-.5z"></path></svg></div><div class="absolute inset-0 flex items-center justify-center"><div class="transition-all opacity-0 scale-50" style="width: 20px; height: 20px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" style="flex-shrink: 0;" class="transition-all opacity-0 scale-50" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M15.188 5.11a.5.5 0 0 1 .752.626l-.056.084-7.5 9a.5.5 0 0 1-.738.033l-3.5-3.5-.064-.078a.501.501 0 0 1 .693-.693l.078.064 3.113 3.113 7.15-8.58z"></path></svg></div></div></div></button></div></div><div class="overflow-x-auto"><pre class="code-block__code !my-0 !rounded-lg !text-sm !leading-relaxed p-3.5" style="color: rgb(20, 24, 31); background: transparent; font-family: var(--font-mono);"><code style="color: rgb(20, 24, 31); background: transparent; font-family: var(--font-mono); white-space: pre-wrap;"><span><span>
</span></span><span>A higher RPI indicates a team consistently converts defensive moments 
</span><span>into forward ball movement.
</span><span>
</span><span>### Supporting metrics
</span><span>- **Average distance progressed per regain** (metres)
</span><span>- **Time to first progressive action** (seconds)
</span><span>- **Regain zone** — where on the pitch the ball was won back
</span><span>- **Outcome of sequence** — shot, chance created, possession retained, lost
</span><span>
</span><span>---
</span><span>
</span><span>## Methodology
</span><span>
</span><span>### 1. Transition Detection
</span><span>- Identify all regain events from StatsBomb event data
</span><span>- Tag each regain with: timestamp, location (x/y), match period, scoreline context
</span><span>
</span><span>### 2. Progression Window
</span><span>- For each regain, extract all events within the following 5 seconds
</span><span>- Classify each event as progressive, lateral, or backward
</span><span>- Calculate distance and direction of ball movement
</span><span>
</span><span>### 3. Phase of Play Context
</span><span>Segment regains by game state:
</span><span>- **Early game** (0–30 min)
</span><span>- **Mid game** (30–60 min)
</span><span>- **Late game** (60–90 min)
</span><span>- **Pressing phase** vs **settled defence**
</span><span>
</span><span>This directly addresses the question of whether context changes 
</span><span>the value and outcome of transitions.
</span><span>
</span><span>### 4. Spatial Analysis
</span><span>Divide the pitch into zones:
</span><span>- Defensive third / Middle third / Attacking third
</span><span>- Left corridor / Central / Right corridor
</span><span>
</span><span>Identify which zones produce the most dangerous transitions 
</span><span>and where Argentina was most vulnerable.
</span><span>
</span><span>### 5. For &amp; Against Comparison
</span><span>Apply the metric to both sides in every match:
</span><span>- Argentina RPI (for)
</span><span>- Opponent RPI (against)
</span><span>
</span><span>This gives a head-to-head transition efficiency comparison 
</span><span>across all 7 World Cup matches.
</span><span>
</span><span>### 6. Player-Level Analysis
</span><span>Identify which players:
</span><span>- Win the most regains
</span><span>- Trigger the most progressive sequences after regains
</span><span>- Are involved in the highest-value transitions
</span><span>
</span><span>---
</span><span>
</span><span>## Data Source
</span><span>
</span><span>**StatsBomb Open Data — FIFA World Cup 2022**
</span><span>- Free and publicly available via the `statsbombpy` Python library
</span><span>- Event-level data including location, timestamp, and action type
</span><span>- Used in accordance with StatsBomb's open data terms
</span><span>
</span><span>---
</span><span>
</span><span>## Expected Visualisations
</span><span>
</span><span>1. **RPI comparison — Argentina vs opponents (bar chart)**
</span><span>   One bar per match, for and against side by side
</span><span>
</span><span>2. **Pitch heatmap — where regains happen**
</span><span>   Spatial distribution of regains across all matches
</span><span>
</span><span>3. **Progression map — direction and distance**
</span><span>   Arrows showing average ball movement in the 5-second window
</span><span>
</span><span>4. **Phase of play breakdown (bar/line chart)**
</span><span>   How RPI changes across match periods — early, mid, late game
</span><span>
</span><span>---
</span><span>
</span><span>## Key Analytical Questions
</span><span>
</span><span>- Does Argentina's transition efficiency increase or decrease 
</span><span>  as matches progress?
</span><span>- Which opponents were most vulnerable to Argentina's transitions?
</span><span>- In which matches was Argentina most exposed in defensive transitions?
</span><span>- Do high-press phases produce more progressive regains than 
</span><span>  settled defensive phases?
</span><span>- Which players are Argentina's transition triggers?
</span><span>
</span><span>---
</span><span>
</span><span>## Limitations
</span><span>
</span><span>- StatsBomb event data does not include physical tracking — 
</span><span>  player movement between events is inferred, not measured
</span><span>- The 5-second window is a fixed threshold — future work could 
</span><span>  explore dynamic windows based on game state
</span><span>- RPI treats all progressive actions equally — a 2-metre 
</span><span>  forward pass and a 30-metre carry both count as one action
</span><span>- Context (score, opponent quality, match importance) is noted 
</span><span>  but not weighted in the base metric
</span><span>
</span><span>---
</span><span>
</span><span>## Connection to Broader Work
</span><span>
</span><span>This project is the second in a connected series:
</span><span>
</span><span>| Project | Focus | Data |
</span><span>|---|---|---|
</span><span>| Off-Ball Movement &amp; Attacking Threat | How runs create value before the ball arrives | SkillCorner (A-League) |
</span><span>| **Regain → Progression (Argentina 2022)** | **How teams capitalise in the 5s after winning the ball** | **StatsBomb (World Cup 2022)** |
</span><span>| Portland Thorns Opposition Analysis | Full match prep framework using both approaches | IMPECT-style event data |
</span><span>
</span><span>The metric used here was originally developed for real opposition 
</span><span>analysis work and is being validated publicly for the first time 
</span><span>in this project.
</span><span>
</span><span>---
</span><span>
</span><span>## Tools &amp; Libraries
</span><span>
</span><span>- Python (pandas, numpy)
</span><span>- statsbombpy
</span><span>- matplotlib / mplsoccer
</span><span>- Google Colab
</span><span>
</span><span>---
</span><span>
</span><span>## Author
</span><span>
</span><span>Yiannis Kastritis
</span><span>MSc Football Data Analytics
</span><span>[LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/in/yiannis-kastritis-a417bb122) | 
</span><span>[GitHub](https://github.com/YIANNIS4)</span></code></pre></div></div>
