ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Here are the detailed steps:</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Step 1 — Download the file</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Scroll up in this chat to the latest <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">index.html</code> file</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click the download button on it</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">It will save as <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">index(3).html</code> or similar — that's fine for now</li>
</ul>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Step 2 — Create your GitHub repo</strong></p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Go to <strong>github.com</strong> and sign in</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click the <strong>+</strong> icon in the top right corner</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>New repository</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">In the repository name field type exactly:
<code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">yiannis-kastritis.github.io</code></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Make sure <strong>Public</strong> is selected</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Leave everything else unticked</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>Create repository</strong></li>
</ol>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Step 3 — Upload the file</strong></p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Once inside the new repo you'll see a page that says "Quick setup"</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>uploading an existing file</strong> (it's a link in the middle of the page)</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Drag your downloaded <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">index.html</code> file into the upload area</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Before committing — look at the filename at the top of the page and make sure it says <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">index.html</code> exactly. If it says <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">index(3).html</code> click on the filename and rename it to <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">index.html</code></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Scroll down to the green <strong>Commit changes</strong> button</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click it</li>
</ol>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Step 4 — Enable GitHub Pages</strong></p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>Settings</strong> in the top menu of your repo</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">In the left sidebar scroll down and click <strong>Pages</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Under <strong>Branch</strong> click the dropdown that says <strong>None</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Select <strong>main</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>Save</strong></li>
</ol>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Step 5 — Wait 2 minutes</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">GitHub will show a box at the top of the Pages section saying your site is being built</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">After 1-2 minutes refresh the page</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">It will show a green box saying:
<strong>"Your site is live at <a class="underline underline underline-offset-2 decoration-1 decoration-current/40 hover:decoration-current focus:decoration-current" href="https://yiannis-kastritis.github.io/">https://yiannis-kastritis.github.io</a>"</strong></li>
</ul>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Step 6 — Add it to LinkedIn</strong></p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Go to your LinkedIn profile</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>Edit profile</strong> (pencil icon)</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>Contact info</strong> (pencil icon)</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Under <strong>Website</strong> add:
<code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">https://yiannis-kastritis.github.io</code></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Set label to <strong>Portfolio</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Save</li>
</ol>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Tell me which step you're on and I'll help you through it.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
