ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Honestly — no, not yet. Here's why:</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>The site is strong because it's focused.</strong>
 Every section earns its place right now. Adding "future goals" risks 
making it look like a CV rather than a portfolio, and it can signal that
 you're still figuring things out rather than already doing them.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>The rule for portfolio sites:</strong>
Show what you've done, not what you plan to do. Actions speak louder 
than intentions — especially to a data company like SkillCorner who will
 judge you on output.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>The one section that could genuinely add value:</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">A short <strong>"Currently working on"</strong> line — not a full section, just one line in the hero or footer. Something like:</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><em>"Currently: Defensive Transition Analysis — Argentina 2022 World Cup"</em></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">That's
 forward-looking without being vague. It shows active momentum and if 
Mike visits the site right now he sees you're already building the next 
thing.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>What will naturally improve the site over time:</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Argentina project added → bump to 4 projects</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Portland Thorns case study added → bump to 5</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Each new project makes the site richer without needing extra sections</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>My honest take:</strong>
The site as it stands is already better than 95% of early-career 
football data analyst portfolios. Don't add sections for the sake of it.
 Add projects instead — they do more work.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Want me to add the "Currently working on" line?</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
