ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Here are the fully detailed steps with descriptions for each:</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Step 1 — Download the file from this chat</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Scroll up in this conversation and find the most recent <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">index.html</code> file I shared</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click the download icon on it</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">It will save to your Downloads folder — probably named <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">index(3).html</code> or similar</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Find it in your Downloads folder and <strong>rename it</strong> to exactly <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">index.html</code> (no brackets, no numbers)</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">On Windows: right click → Rename. On Mac: click once slowly on the filename → type new name. On phone: long press → Rename</li>
</ul>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Step 2 — Sign in to GitHub</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Open your browser and go to <strong>github.com</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>Sign in</strong> in the top right</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Enter your username and password</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">You should land on your GitHub homepage showing your existing repos</li>
</ul>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Step 3 — Create a new repository</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">A repository (repo) is just a folder on GitHub that stores your files. You need one specifically named for GitHub Pages to work.</p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click the <strong>+</strong> icon in the top right corner of the page</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>New repository</strong> from the dropdown</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">You'll see a form — fill it in like this:
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Repository name:</strong> type exactly <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">yiannis-kastritis.github.io</code> — this specific name tells GitHub this is a website</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Description:</strong> optionally type "Personal portfolio website"</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Public / Private:</strong> make sure <strong>Public</strong> is selected — if it's Private the site won't work</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Leave <strong>Add a README</strong>, <strong>Add .gitignore</strong>, and <strong>Choose a license</strong> all unticked</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click the green <strong>Create repository</strong> button at the bottom</li>
</ol>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Step 4 — Upload your file</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">After creating the repo you'll land on a page that says "Quick setup". This looks a bit confusing but don't worry.</p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Look for the text that says <strong>"uploading an existing file"</strong> — it's a clickable blue link in the middle of the page</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click it — you'll see an upload page with a big dashed box</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Open your Downloads folder separately and find your <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">index.html</code> file</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Drag the file</strong> from your Downloads folder into the dashed box on GitHub — or click <strong>choose your files</strong> to browse and select it manually</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">You'll see the file appear in the box with a green checkmark — that means it uploaded successfully</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Check the filename</strong> — at the top of the upload area it should show <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">index.html</code>. If it shows anything else like <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">index(3).html</code> click on it and correct it</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Scroll down the page — you'll see a section called <strong>Commit changes</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Leave the commit message as the default ("Add files via upload")</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click the green <strong>Commit changes</strong> button</li>
</ol>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Your file is now saved on GitHub.</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Step 5 — Enable GitHub Pages</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">GitHub Pages is the feature that turns your file into a live website. It's off by default so you need to switch it on.</p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">You should now be inside your repo seeing your <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">index.html</code> file listed</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>Settings</strong> in the top menu bar of the repo (it has a gear icon)</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">On the left sidebar, scroll down until you see <strong>Pages</strong> — click it</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">You'll see a section called <strong>Build and deployment</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Under <strong>Source</strong> make sure it says <strong>Deploy from a branch</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Under <strong>Branch</strong> you'll see a dropdown currently showing <strong>None</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click that dropdown and select <strong>main</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">A second dropdown appears saying <strong>/ (root)</strong> — leave that as it is</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>Save</strong></li>
</ol>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">GitHub will now start building your website. This takes 1–3 minutes.</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Step 6 — Get your live link</strong></p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Stay on the Pages settings page and wait 1–2 minutes</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Refresh the page</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">You'll see a green box at the top saying:
<strong>"Your site is live at <a class="underline underline underline-offset-2 decoration-1 decoration-current/40 hover:decoration-current focus:decoration-current" href="https://yiannis-kastritis.github.io/">https://yiannis-kastritis.github.io</a>"</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click that link — your portfolio website will open in the browser</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">If it shows a 404 error, wait another minute and refresh again — it sometimes takes a little longer</li>
</ol>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Step 7 — Add the link to LinkedIn</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Now that your site is live, put the URL everywhere it matters.</p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Go to <strong>linkedin.com</strong> and sign in</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click your profile photo → <strong>View profile</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click the <strong>pencil icon</strong> near the top of your profile to edit</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Scroll down to <strong>Contact info</strong> → click the pencil icon next to it</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">You'll see a <strong>Websites</strong> section — click <strong>Add website</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Paste <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">https://yiannis-kastritis.github.io</code> in the URL field</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">In the dropdown next to it change <strong>Other</strong> to <strong>Portfolio</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>Apply</strong> then <strong>Save</strong></li>
</ol>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Your LinkedIn profile will now show your portfolio link publicly.</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Step 8 — Update your GitHub profile bio</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">While you're at it, add the link to your GitHub profile too so anyone who finds your repos can find your full site.</p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Go to <strong>github.com</strong> and make sure you're signed in</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click your profile photo → <strong>Your profile</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>Edit profile</strong> on the left side</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">In the <strong>Website</strong> field paste <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">https://yiannis-kastritis.github.io</code></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>Save</strong></li>
</ol>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">That's it. Tell me which step you're on and I'll help you through it.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
