<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">This works because:</p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">The title is clean and searchable</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">The description mentions SkillCorner and StatsBomb — two names that mean something to anyone in sports data</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">It calls out the live Streamlit app which is a differentiator</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Anyone from SkillCorner who visits your profile will see it immediately without clicking anything</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Let me know once it's up!</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
