<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Fix 3 — Try on desktop instead of mobile</strong>
If you're on your phone, switch to a laptop or desktop browser and try 
from there — LinkedIn's mobile app has more saving bugs than the desktop
 version.</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Fix 4 — Clear cache and retry</strong></p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Clear your browser cache and cookies</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Sign back into LinkedIn</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Try adding the link again</li>
</ol>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Fix 5 — Try adding it through a different section</strong>
Instead of Featured, try:</p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Edit your <strong>intro section</strong> (pencil icon at top of profile)</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Scroll down to <strong>Website URL</strong> field inside the intro editor</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Paste your URL there and save</li>
</ol>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">But honestly — is your website actually deployed and live yet at <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">https://yiannis-kastritis.github.io</code>? Because if the site isn't live yet, LinkedIn may be rejecting the URL because it can't verify it exists.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">That would be the most likely reason for a save failure. Have you completed the GitHub Pages deployment steps?</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
