ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Ah yes — that's exactly it! LinkedIn sometimes blocks you from adding the same URL twice in different sections.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Simple fix:</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Since it's already saved in your Contact info, just add your <strong>Streamlit app</strong> to the Featured section instead — that's actually a better use of Featured anyway because:</p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">The Streamlit app is more visually impressive as a featured card</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">It shows a live interactive tool — much more eye-catching than a plain website link</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Your portfolio website is already findable via Contact info</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>So your Featured section becomes:</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Card 1</strong> → Streamlit live app</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Card 2</strong> → Your best LinkedIn post (your off-ball movement project post)</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Pinning
 your best project post as a Featured card is also very effective — it 
keeps it visible permanently at the top of your profile regardless of 
when you posted it.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Try adding the Streamlit URL to Featured now:</p>
