ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Good thinking on both. Let me address each:</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>On your LinkedIn current position:</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">You're
 right not to list Athenians as your current role — it could look 
misleading if someone asks about it in an interview. You have two honest
 options:</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Option 1 — Keep NHS as current role, add football separately</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Current role: Diabetes Specialist Nurse — NHS</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Then list your football experience below as separate entries without "current" ticked</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">This is the most accurate representation</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Option 2 — List yourself as a Football Data Analyst (Freelance/Independent)</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Current role: Football Data Analyst — Independent/Self-employed</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">This is legitimate given your portfolio, MSc, and actual analytical work</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Keeps the football positioning front and centre</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">NHS stays on your profile below as previous experience</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>My honest recommendation:</strong>
Option 2 is better for your goal of getting hired in football data. 
Anyone searching LinkedIn for analysts will find you. Just make sure 
your about section makes the context clear — that you're transitioning 
from healthcare into football data full time.</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>On the Featured section:</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">The save failure earlier was likely because the URL wasn't live yet. Now that your site should be deployed, try again:</p>
