<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">After
 that, your repo will show the link as a clickable URL directly under 
the About description — anyone who lands on your GitHub profile or this 
repo can click straight through to your website instantly.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">It will look like this on your repo:</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>About</strong>
Personal portfolio website
🌐 yiannis-kastritis.github.io</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">That's
 the standard way all professional GitHub profiles display their 
portfolio link. Takes 30 seconds — do it now while you're there.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
