<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>To use this:</strong></p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Right click the image → <strong>Save image as</strong> → save as <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">og-image.png</code></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Upload it to your GitHub repo alongside <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">index.html</code></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Then tell me and I'll add the meta tags to your <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">index.html</code> so LinkedIn picks it up automatically as the preview thumbnail</li>
